body:
@paco that's a fairly unfair and disingenuous comment.

We ask you to put it into a gist when you open the issue. We've had to ask you several times to follow the steps in the repository when opening the issue. If the information is in the correct format it actually saves us time in analysing and responding. If we have to do this for you, it wastes time we can spend elsewhere.

We work with GitHub from our phones so that we can answer issues out of our normal working hours. This gives you quick responses that would otherwise have to wait until the next working day. The more information you provide, in a format we can work with, the quicker and more accurate our response. Just to be clear I'm writing this from GitHub mobile right now as I'm on holiday.
